TASK_ID=24
TASK_TITLE=Remote detection + auto-tunnel for localhost URLs
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_CREATED=1743321600
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_DESCRIPTION=When Doey runs on a remote server (e.g. Hetzner), detect it automatically and start a tunnel so the user can access dev server URLs (localhost:3000 etc) from their local browser. Two parts: (1) Detection — check for SSH_CLIENT or SSH_TTY env vars. Export DOEY_REMOTE=1 when detected so all hooks/scripts can branch on it. Set this in on-session-start.sh or session env. (2) Auto-tunnel — when DOEY_REMOTE=1, auto-start a tunnel (cloudflared is preferred if available, fall back to bore or similar). Surface the public tunnel URL in the dashboard info panel and/or desktop notification. Add config option to disable or configure tunnel tool. Must work on fresh install — if no tunnel binary is found, warn but don't fail.
TASK_TAGS=infrastructure,hooks,dashboard,config,shell
TASK_TEAM=W2
TASK_LOG_1774855954=DISPATCHED: Sent to W2 Manager
TASK_LOG_1774857027=COMPLETE: Committed ff852ae. 5 source files + 1 new file, bash 3.2 compat pass.
TASK_RESULT=Remote detection via SSH env vars, auto-tunnel with cloudflared/ngrok/bore, info panel display, config options.
TASK_FILES=shell/doey.sh,shell/doey-tunnel.sh,.claude/hooks/on-session-start.sh,shell/doey-config-default.sh,shell/info-panel.sh
